            <table cellpadding="2" cellspacing="2" style="width: 100%">
             <tr>
              <td>
               <span id="ctl00_cphlocationstitle_titleofct" style="font-weight:bold;">
                How To Select A Moving Company
               </span>
              </td>
             </tr>
             <tr>
              <td>
               <span id="ctl00_cphlocationstitle_summaryofct">
               </span>
              </td>
             </tr>
             <tr>
              <td>
               <span id="ctl00_cphlocationstitle_postct">
                <p>
                 You have finally been offered the promotion of your dreams. You have been waiting for what feels like forever and it has finally come. Theres only one problem: its at the office on the other side of the state. You have 30 days to find a new home and get moved in. While this may seem like a serious time crunch, try not to worry.
                 <a href="http://www.allmysons.com/jacksonville/">
                  Jacksonville movers
                 </a>
                 can get your items packed and moved in no time at all. Once you have found your home, hiring professional movers can ensure that you get moved in by your deadline. There are a lot of moving companies out there, so its important to make sure you find one with the following qualities.
                </p>
                <p>
                 Experience
                </p>
                <p>
                 When looking for a moving company, look for one that has experience. You want this for a couple of reasons. The first reason is simply because the more experience they have, the less likely they are to make mistakes and break or lose your items. Finding one with experience means that they have learned the best way to do things, and have learned from their mistakes in the past. The second reason for finding a company with experience is because that way you can do some research on them. You can ask friends, neighbors, or even conduct an online search to find out as much as you can about the moving company. The longer they have been in business, the easier it will be to find out what kind of moving company they are.
                </p>
                <p>
                 The Right Equipment
                </p>
                <p>
                 Another thing that your Jacksonville movers should have is all of the equipment necessary to make your move as smooth of a transition as possible. This means providing the little things such as boxes, packing tape, and bubble wrap. If you have larger items that need moved, such as a piano or a refrigerator, its important to make sure they have the right materials to help them move those items, to not only reduce the risk of injury but to reduce the risk of your items being damaged. If they do have those items, make sure that the price of those is included in your estimate. You dont want to be overcharged for something that you werent aware was going to cost extra.
                </p>
                <p>
                 Insurance
                </p>
                <p>
                 Perhaps the most important thing to look for when selecting a moving company is one that has insurance. You want to be covered if any of your items get lost or damaged during the move. Of course, your movers should do everything possible to keep this from happening, but mistakes do happen even with the most professional of movers. Find out how much coverage they have so you know whether or not you are going to need to buy more coverage.
                </p>
                <p>
                 If you find a moving company that has a lot of experience, good customer reviews, the right equipment, and insurance, then chances are you have found a moving company that will provide you with the satisfaction and service that you need and deserve. Moving doesnt have to be an overly stressful process, let Jacksonville movers do all the hard work so that you can get into your new home as soon as possible.
                </p>
               </span>
              </td>
